# RFC companion documentation gate (required)

Umbraculum commits architecture in **RFCs** and records as-built shape in **companion docs** (module surfaces, horizontal surfaces, audits, build logs). Implementing from RFC prose alone causes drift — CI encodes code gates more strongly than doc completeness unless agents enforce companions.

## When this rule fires

- Implementing or reviewing features tied to an **accepted RFC**, especially [RFC-0001](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/rfcs/0001-modules-tiers-governance-and-automation-placement.md) §8.2 rows (rendering, notifications, validation, modules).
- Adding `registerModule({ documentTemplates })`, render-job routes, or `render_document` consumers.
- Amending governance that affects downstream module obligations.

Does **not** require reading every RFC for unrelated typos or docs-only edits with no RFC tie.

## Required reading order

1. RFC **§1 Summary** (the commits in bullets).
2. [`docs/rfcs/README.md`](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/rfcs/README.md) §3 — artifact taxonomy.
3. Row for that RFC in [`docs/design/rfc-companion-documentation-audit.md`](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/design/rfc-companion-documentation-audit.md).
4. Linked **horizontal** or **module surface** doc(s) for the RFC (e.g. `canonical-document-rendering-surface.md` for RFC-0007).

## Required write discipline

| Change | Companion update |
|--------|------------------|
| New `documentTemplates` / template ref | [`canonical-document-rendering-surface.md`](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/design/canonical-document-rendering-surface.md) §2 registry |
| New canonical module surface | `docs/design/canonical-<code>-module-surface.md` |
| RFC-0008 delivery behavior | [`canonical-notifications-outbound-delivery-surface.md`](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/design/canonical-notifications-outbound-delivery-surface.md) |

Same PR as the code when possible; otherwise a docs-only PR immediately before merge.

## Companion skill

Use `rfc-companion-doc-audit` skill for a bounded OK/FAIL pass on RFC number(s) before declaring a wave complete.

## Repo without these paths

If the active repo has no `docs/design/rfc-companion-documentation-audit.md`, this rule is informational — do not block. Umbraculum-family repos are expected to carry the audit matrix.
